===Etymology 1===
[[Image:Biber-drawing.jpg|thumb|Beavers]]
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{m|enm|bever}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|beofor||beaver}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*bebruz||beaver}} (compare West Frisian {{m|fy|bever}}, Dutch {{m|nl|bever}}, French {{m|fr|bièvre}}, German {{m|de|Biber}}, dialectal Swedish {{m|sv|bjur}}), from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{m|ine-pro|*bʰébʰrus||beaver}} (compare {{cog|cy|befer}}, {{cog|la|fiber}}, {{cog|lt|bẽbras}}, {{cog|ru|бобр|}}, {{cog|ae|||tr=bawra}}, {{m|ae|||tr=bawri}} {{rfscript|ae}}, {{cog|sa|बभ्रु||tr=bábhru|mongoose; ichneumon}}), from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{m|ine-pro|*bʰreu-||shining, brown}}. Related to [[brown]] and [[bear]].

